import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['precipitation'].plot(kind='hist', bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['precipitation'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['precipitation'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['precipitation'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['precipitation'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of precipitation?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.plot(data['date'], data['temp_max'], label='temp_max')
    ax.plot(data['date'], data['temp_min'], label='temp_min')
    ax.legend()
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('Temperature')
    ax.set_title('How does temperature vary over time?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
